1
00:00:05,980 --> 00:00:10,420
How to go on
in the absence of Kṛṣṇa.

2
00:00:10,504 --> 00:00:13,694
[Devotee of the Devotee of Krisha]

3
00:00:13,694 --> 00:00:21,132
And interestingly this is the very,
very high subject matter

4
00:00:21,132 --> 00:00:24,272
of the depths of separation,
expressed there,

5
00:00:24,272 --> 00:00:30,062
in the conclusion of Śikṣāṣṭaka,
the conclusion of Caitanya-caritāmṛta,

6
00:00:30,062 --> 00:00:35,260
very very high and deep things.
But miraculously, mysteriously

7
00:00:35,260 --> 00:00:45,380
it’s also relevant to those
in the aspiring position—adarśan.

8
00:00:45,380 --> 00:00:49,576
Adarśanān marma-hatāṁ karotu vā
[CC: 3.20.47]—how to go on,

9
00:00:49,576 --> 00:00:54,849
how to pursue Kṛṣṇa consciousness
in the apparent absence of Kṛṣṇa,

10
00:00:54,849 --> 00:00:58,591
in the apparent absence
of Kṛṣṇa consciousness.

11
00:00:58,971 --> 00:01:02,375
It’s the critical point.

12
00:01:03,695 --> 00:01:09,995
Śrīla Guru Mahārāj 
[is] saying that

13
00:01:09,995 --> 00:01:15,851
if you can honestly, candidly
acknowledge and admit,

14
00:01:15,851 --> 00:01:22,388
that you are not Kṛṣṇa conscious,
you have no Kṛṣṇa consciousness,

15
00:01:22,388 --> 00:01:25,601
or as the great devotees
sometimes, they’ll say,

16
00:01:25,601 --> 00:01:29,981
“I’m going 
in the opposite direction.”

17
00:01:30,091 --> 00:01:33,103
That’s also in these verses.

18
00:01:33,103 --> 00:01:35,585
Rādhārāṇī and Vraja-gopīs—
they’re sometimes saying,

19
00:01:35,585 --> 00:01:38,328
“They were better off before
they’ve met Kṛṣṇa.”

20
00:01:38,328 --> 00:01:40,438
[Laughing]

21
00:01:40,438 --> 00:01:44,083
So devotees’s thinking like that.
And Guru Mahārāj said,

22
00:01:44,083 --> 00:01:49,873
“So if you can think like that—
honestly, candidly, assess yourself,

23
00:01:49,873 --> 00:01:56,895
and say, ‘I appear to be untouched
by Kṛṣṇa consciousness.’”

24
00:01:56,895 --> 00:02:00,758
He said,
“But, at the same time …

25
00:02:00,758 --> 00:02:03,878
but I have no other shelter.

26
00:02:03,878 --> 00:02:07,538
I have no other Lord than Kṛṣṇa,
and no other interest

27
00:02:07,538 --> 00:02:12,553
than this association,
and service of His devotees.”

28
00:02:12,553 --> 00:02:18,193
He said, 
“Then you might be a devotee.”

29
00:02:18,193 --> 00:02:27,033
And there’s nothing greater, better than
being a devotee of a devotee of Kṛṣṇa.

30
00:02:27,041 --> 00:02:32,371
gopī-bhartuḥ pada-kamalayor
dāsa-dāsānudāsaḥ [Cc: 2.13.80]—

31
00:02:32,372 --> 00:02:35,482
that’s also from Mahāprabhu.

